I used it to treat my LHT frame before I built it up, and recently
used it on a (cheap) nashbar steel MTB frame that I am building up as
an Xtracycle.  Worth it to me for the little bit of additional peace
of mind.  You can get moisture inside a frame not only from the
obvious sources like riding in the rain, but from condensation due to
temperature changes - bike stored inside then taken outside for the
ride, for example.

Needed?  Probably not absolutely needed.  Any steel frame will
probably out-live me at this point even without any kind of rust-
proofing.  It is such a simple and inexpensive part of the build,
though, so why not?

Chuck

