Unfortunately I noticed one minor barrier (literally) in my LHT and
that is in the area of the chain stay junction and the bottom bracket
shell. While there is a hole in the shell its smaller than the chain
stay and that creates essentially a wall for water to pool up. I
thought about grinding or drilling the area right at the bottom of
that hole lower to help let water drain down the chain stay and into
the bottom bracket and out a drain hole, which I would also have to
drill. Being that this barrier forms a little area for water to
collect right at a weld joint I'll just about bet there will be
problems there in the future for some owners.  The down tube suffers
from the same issue. On a lugged frame the tubing just fits within the
lug letting water drain to the lowest point but a tigged frame with
tubes butted up to the shell and welded, creates a barrier or a &quot;dam&quot;
for water to pool and rust the weld joint. Of course any modification
to the frame would probably void the warranty but I am concerned about
this on my frame. Whether from condensation or road water this could
be a problem for quite a few welded steel bike frames (of any brand)
that use high quality thin walled tubing.

